# Software Requirements Specification (SRS)

**Project Name:** TaskFlow
**Version:** 1.0

---

## 1. Introduction

This Software Requirements Specification (SRS) document outlines the functional and non-functional requirements for the TaskFlow Task Management System (Version 1.0). It describes what the system will do, how it will perform, and the constraints under which it must operate, serving as the primary requirements document for system design, implementation, and testing.

### 1.1 Purpose

The purpose of this document is to clearly define the system requirements for the TaskFlow web application. It is intended to be read by:

* **The Client (TaskFlow Solutions Ltd.):** To verify that the development team fully understands their business needs and operational challenges.
* **The Development Team (Nexus Software Solutions):** To serve as the definitive blueprint for coding and database design.
* **Quality Assurance (QA) Testers:** To provide a basis for creating test cases and verifying that the final product meets the agreed-upon standards.

### 1.2 Document Scope

The TaskFlow system is a modern, responsive web-based application designed to replace disconnected manual tools (Excel, WhatsApp, email) with a centralized platform. The primary goal is to improve team collaboration, provide real-time visibility into project progress, and streamline reporting.

**In-Scope Functionality:**
The initial release of the software will include:

* The system shall provide functionality for managing users and organizing them into teams, enforcing role-based access control (RBAC).
* The system shall allow authorized users to create, configure, and manage project lifecycles.
* The system shall enable users to create, assign, update, and track individual tasks within projects.
* The system shall provide real-time dashboards for managers to monitor project progress and identify bottlenecks instantly.
* The system shall facilitate collaboration through task-specific commenting threads and automated notifications for approaching deadlines and updates.
* The system shall generate automated project status and individual performance reports.
* The system shall enforce secure authentication and authorization mechanisms to protect company data.

**Out-of-Scope Exclusions:**
To ensure timely delivery and prevent scope creep, the following are explicitly excluded from this release:

* Native mobile applications (iOS/Android). The system will rely exclusively on a responsive web interface.
* Automated data migration from legacy spreadsheets or messaging apps.
* Integration with third-party platforms (e.g., Jira, Slack, or external calendar APIs).
* Advanced HR modules, including payroll, timesheets, and client billing.

### 1.3 Definitions, Acronyms, and Abbreviations

| Term / Acronym | Definition |
| :--- | :--- |
| **SRS** | Software Requirements Specification. |
| **User** | Any authenticated person using the system. |
| **Manager** | A user responsible for overseeing one or more projects. |
| **Team** | A group of users assigned to work together. |
| **Task** | A distinct, assignable piece of work with a defined priority, status, and deadline. |
| **Project** | A collection of related tasks assigned to a specific team or set of users to achieve a business goal. |
| **Dashboard** | A user interface that organizes and presents real-time information and key metrics in an easy-to-read format. |
| **Notification** | A system-generated message informing users of important events. |
| **Authentication** | Verification of a user's identity. |
| **Authorization** | Determination of what an authenticated user is allowed to do. |
| **RBAC** | Role-Based Access Control; a method of restricting system access based on the role of the user. |

